        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezlise</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-10-99 10:51 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Although everybody has probably heard that this is done, TWICE recently people have tried to pass sawed-off feet as "valuable" to me. Once at a flea market, once at an antique store. And one of these pez was the brand new Easter Bunny! (I had to keep a straight face when I saw that one.) In all fairness, the antique store was a co-op and the owner said he thought they were fake, as he was showing them to me. How does everybody else feel about this? Would you point it out? I did. The guy at the flea market didn't say much when I did. Something like "Oh". So you know he was gonna keep that pez right there on his table. Obviously, the biggest thing is always "know what you are buying".</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezdrake</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-10-99 05:45 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Is nothing sacred? This is one thing I am pretty ambivalent about. Nonfooted or footed - makes no difference to me. I collect the different dispensers and that is based on the head. I feel like pointing out that this is the result of people paying a ridiculous amount of more money for non-footed than footed pez. It would really piss me off if I bought a pez that was mutilated. I would prefer to just buy a footed baloo than a sawed off one to make it look "more valuable".<br>
            Pezdrake</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezdrake</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-14-99 06:15 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Well, today I went to a flea market looking for Pez (of course) and I saw a Garfield there with the feet cut off. I don't think the guy running it had a clue about PEZ and pez values and I don't think he intentionally did it but I thought it was pretty funny and sad that someone ever even tried to do that. Then again, maybe the feet just broke off innocently...</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezlise</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-15-99 07:45 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Right, you don't know. I think some dealers just know no feet means more money, maybe that's why they are trying it? I guess with anything popular someone will always try to pull a fast one...</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Alex</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-15-99 09:42 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">i knew someone once who was sawing off feet with a razorblade.. it was amazing how flawless it looked.. i've been collecting for 8yrs now and i would have been fooled easily if i didn't know that the dispensers he was doing it to were never made without feet... needless to say i went ballistic on him... ...i can't imagine the thought of all these dealers damaging pez when the collectors are never gonna fall for it.. it's a shame</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>suzpez</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-24-99 09:03 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I got taken on a no foot Winnie the Pooh. I figured it out when I tried to put shoes on him. They didn't fit! The way to tell if the feet have been sawed off is that the pez with feet have a thicker "spine" down the back, while the true no foot pez have a thin one. Take a look at your pez at home to see the difference.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>joquel</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 11-24-99 09:36 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Hey SUSPEZ</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Sorry about your misfortune. I hope you are at least able to get your money back. Was it a dealer we need to be aware of.</font></p>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I will start checking my Pez when I start purchasing footless Pez.</font></p>
          </td>
